WEBVTT

00:00.769 --> 00:02.180
The Carmichael Show is taped

00:02.181 --> 00:03.903
in front of a live studio audience.

00:06.106 --> 00:08.141
Hey, uh, where did we get this table from?

00:08.143 --> 00:10.811
Fell off the back of a truck.

00:10.812 --> 00:12.446
Wait a minute, you stole this?

00:12.447 --> 00:13.614
No, I didn't steal it.

00:13.615 --> 00:16.350
It actually fell off the back of a truck.

00:16.351 --> 00:18.652
Almost killed me and your daddy.

00:18.653 --> 00:21.322
Mm-hmm. We agreed not to
sue if they let us keep it.

00:21.323 --> 00:23.290
Wait, wait, wait, wait. Why
didn't y'all just sue him?

00:23.291 --> 00:24.692
You would have got way more.

00:24.693 --> 00:26.927
Well, we were young and dumb, Bobby.

00:26.928 --> 00:28.596
Hey, everyone.

00:28.597 --> 00:31.465
Yeah, hey, everybody. So, uh,

00:31.466 --> 00:33.934
why's the good table
out? What's going on here?

00:33.935 --> 00:36.203
- What are you two doing here?
- No, no, no, no...

00:36.204 --> 00:37.838
you answer my question first.

00:37.839 --> 00:39.807
Are you planning a fancy dinner without me?

00:39.808 --> 00:41.841
Yes.

00:43.010 --> 00:44.478
Now you answer my question.

00:44.479 --> 00:46.146
Why are you here?

00:46.147 --> 00:47.681
Well, I thought we were
going to the movies,

00:47.682 --> 00:49.416
but then Jerrod saw Bobby's car,

00:49.417 --> 00:52.319
and I'm not saying he's jealous, but...

00:52.320 --> 00:53.587
here we are.

00:53.588 --> 00:55.122
Well, what's going on here,

00:55.123 --> 00:56.991
for real? Bobby, you know
you can't keep a secret.

00:56.992 --> 00:58.192
Tell me... what's up?

00:58.193 --> 01:00.794
- Reverend Carlson coming over.
- Oh, Bobby.

01:00.795 --> 01:02.229
The reverend's coming over?

01:02.230 --> 01:03.831
- You know I love the reverend.
- No, no,

01:03.832 --> 01:06.901
I do not want you challenging
the reverend the way you do.

01:06.902 --> 01:09.303
You know, you're the same
kid who shut down Bible study

01:09.304 --> 01:12.106
with your theory of evolution.

01:12.107 --> 01:15.676
You realize it's not just my theory, right?

01:15.677 --> 01:17.645
Okay, uh, who's this reverend?

01:17.646 --> 01:19.079
He's been the reverend at my church

01:19.080 --> 01:20.981
since before these boys were born. He has

01:20.982 --> 01:23.317
stuck with us through thick and thin.

01:23.318 --> 01:24.652
Oh, he's a good man.

01:24.653 --> 01:26.954
A bit of a drinker.

01:26.955 --> 01:30.323
But in a good way. You
know, like Ted Kennedy.

01:31.125 --> 01:33.827
Reverend Carlson marched with Dr. King.

01:33.828 --> 01:35.062
Yeah, okay,

01:35.063 --> 01:37.431
but, Ma, a lot of people
marched with Dr. King.

01:37.432 --> 01:41.067
Yeah, but he was in the
VIP. He had backstage passes.

01:43.370 --> 01:44.805
Now listen,

01:44.806 --> 01:46.774
the reverend is gonna be here in a moment.

01:46.775 --> 01:48.642
Now, if you two are gonna stay for dinner,

01:48.643 --> 01:52.546
listen up. My reputation at
the church is on the line,

01:52.547 --> 01:54.615
so I want you all

01:54.616 --> 01:57.017
to keep your sins to yourselves.

01:57.018 --> 01:58.919
Be clear with us, Ma...

01:58.920 --> 02:00.754
what are our sins, exactly?

02:00.755 --> 02:04.325
Well, yours is standing right next to you.

02:04.326 --> 02:05.993
It's called living in sin.

02:05.994 --> 02:07.027
It's in the title.

02:07.028 --> 02:09.697
Oh. No offense, baby.

02:09.698 --> 02:11.532
Nah. I'm a sin, I'm naughty.

02:11.533 --> 02:13.766
I'm just trying to get through this.

02:16.437 --> 02:18.505
Wait, we are embarrassing,
but Bobby's here?

02:18.506 --> 02:20.541
Bobby lives with his ex-wife
and her new boyfriend.

02:20.542 --> 02:22.775
Hey, hey, he got a name, Jerrod.

02:24.645 --> 02:26.981
Which I want you to keep to yourself.

02:26.982 --> 02:29.249
Do not say anything about your divorce

02:29.250 --> 02:30.517
in front of the reverend.

02:30.518 --> 02:32.686
So you want all of us
to lie to the reverend?

02:32.687 --> 02:33.988
No. Not lie.

02:33.989 --> 02:36.090
Just omit...

02:36.091 --> 02:38.258
all the bad truths.

02:38.259 --> 02:40.461
Well, you know what I say...
nothing wrong with a little lie,

02:40.462 --> 02:42.329
long as it makes you sound more impressive.

02:42.330 --> 02:44.298
- Joe.
- Well, I mean, I get tired

02:44.299 --> 02:45.833
of telling people I'm a truck driver.

02:45.834 --> 02:49.168
Once in a while I say I'm a airplane pilot.

02:50.571 --> 02:52.306
All right, Dad, let me
keep it real with you, okay?

02:52.307 --> 02:54.074
You don't have a voice
to be no airline pilot.

02:54.075 --> 02:55.309
What are you talking about?

02:55.310 --> 02:57.277
Feel free to move about the cabin.

02:57.278 --> 02:59.078
That's not comforting to you?

03:00.648 --> 03:03.684
Joe, no lying to the reverend.

03:03.685 --> 03:05.918
Fine. I won't lie.

03:07.287 --> 03:09.555
That's a lie. I'm gonna lie.

03:11.325 --> 03:13.093
Okay, it sounds like there's,
like, a lot of pressure

03:13.094 --> 03:15.062
- having dinner with the reverend.
- No, no pressure at all.

03:15.063 --> 03:16.997
Just relax and just be yourself, okay?

03:16.998 --> 03:18.899
Yeah, we love you for you, Maxine.

03:18.900 --> 03:22.636
Okay, I can't tell if
you're lying to me or not.

03:22.637 --> 03:25.771
I'm pretty good, right?

03:28.642 --> 03:30.377
Oh, my goodness, he's here!

03:30.378 --> 03:32.646
Now, Jerrod, no living in sin.

03:32.647 --> 03:35.082
Joe, no lying. And-and, Bobby,

03:35.083 --> 03:36.717
no facts about your life at all,

03:36.718 --> 03:38.986
because they're all sad.

03:38.987 --> 03:41.855
Sad, sad, sad.

03:41.856 --> 03:43.824
Okay, wait, is there...

03:43.825 --> 03:45.392
is there anything that I need to do?

03:45.393 --> 03:48.195
Well, uh, just don't go
around telling everybody

03:48.196 --> 03:51.231
that you're pro-choice and all that.

03:51.232 --> 03:53.667
Cynthia, you and I have
never even discussed that.

03:53.668 --> 03:55.201
But you are, aren't you?

03:55.969 --> 03:57.370
Uh-huh.

03:59.440 --> 04:01.909
Oh, Reverend Carlson!

04:01.910 --> 04:04.478
Ah, the Carmichaels.

04:04.479 --> 04:07.014
Uh, they had a two-for-one special.

04:07.015 --> 04:09.717
God saves those who save.

04:09.718 --> 04:12.553
Yes, he does. Yes, he does.

04:12.554 --> 04:14.188
Hey, I want you to meet
my girlfriend, Maxine.

04:14.189 --> 04:15.756
- Oh, pleasure.
- Yeah, yeah.

04:15.757 --> 04:18.425
We live together.

04:18.426 --> 04:19.927
Oh, come on.

04:19.928 --> 04:22.196
- You didn't know I was gonna do that?
- Oh!

